Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
open_schematic(25.10)                                    open_schematic(25.10)

Name
       open_schematic  - Opens the schematic view of the specified or selected
       objects

Syntax
       open_schematic

       [-help]

       [-name <string>]

       [-objects <<inst | net | instTerm | term | hinst>>+ | -selected]

       [-type {module cone}]

       Opens the schematic view of the specified or selected objects.  By  de-
       fault, the schematic opens in the flattened (cone) mode.

Parameters
       -help  Prints  out the command usage. For a detailed description of the
              command, use the man command:

              man open_schematic

       -name <string>
              Specifies a unique window name for  the  schematic  view  to  be
              opened.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -objects <inst | net | <instTerm | term | hinst>>+
              Specifies the object(s) to be added in the schematic view.

              If  multiple  objects are specified, the Schematic Viewer can be
              opened only in the flattened mode (-type cone).

              Note: This option cannot be used with -type module.

              Data_type: (inst|net|instTerm|term|hinst)+, optional

       -selected
              Specifies that the selected object(s) are to  be  added  in  the
              schematic view.

              If  multiple  objects  are selected, the Schematic Viewer can be
              opened only in the flattened mode (-type cone).

              Note: This option cannot be used with -objects or -type module.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -type {module cone}
              Specifies the type of schematic to be  opened.  If  you  specify
              cone,  the  tool opens the Schematic Viewer to display schematic
              in the flattened mode. If you specify module, the tool opens the
              Schematic Viewer to display schematic in the hierarchical mode.

              Default: cone

              Data_type: enum, optional

Examples
              * The following command opens the schematic  for  the  specified
                instance in the hierarchical mode:

                open_schematic -objects ram1/subram02_lower/TESTACT_INST_PERI-
                WDSRAM001PAA512W27C3/U202

              * The  following  command  opens the schematic for the specified
                instance in the flattened mode:

                open_schematic -objects ram1/subram02_lower/TESTACT_INST_PERI-
                WDSRAM001PAA512W27C3/U202 -type module

              * The following command opens the schematic for the selected ob-
                ject in the flattened mode:

                open_schematic -selected

              * The following command opens the  schematic  for  multiple  se-
                lected objects in the flattened mode:

                open_schematic -selected

